               <p>SECOND COUNT, stating it to be the property of some person unknown.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-127-person1360">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CLARE
               <interp inst="t18190421-127-person1360" type="surname" value="CLARE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-127-person1360" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-127-person1360" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable of the Thames Police. On the 27th of March, about half-past six o'clock in the morning, I stopped the prisoner at the gate of the Docks, and asked him what he had got in his hat? he said, nothing at all. I took it off, and he then said he had a little pepper. I took him into custody, and found a night cap tied round his body, with 5 lbs. of pepper in it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ARABIN. Q. He had been in his barge all night - A. Yes, it was laden with pepper.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It was sweepings.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190421-127-verdict698" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18190421-127-verdict698" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190421-127-punish699" type="punishmentDescription">
